1
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,320
I'm coming.

2
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,000
Jingu.

3
00:01:59,080 --> 00:01:59,720
Auntie.

4
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,900
You are back again.

5
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,920
Auntie, I lost my house key.

6
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,360
I don't know if I forgot it

7
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,960
or left it in Qingyun's room.

8
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,840
Then come in, come in.

9
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,400
Let's look for it together. Come.

10
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,000
Okay.

11
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,930
Could your key have fallen into my underwear?

12
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,160
I mean,

13
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,280
did you even bring it at all?

14
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,240
It's too late today.

15
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,720
Why don't you go back first,

16
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,200
and I'll keep looking for it.

17
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:54,260
If I find it, I'll have Qingyun bring it to you tomorrow.

18
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:56,210
But my parents went to Beijing.

19
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,760
If I can't find the house key,

20
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,760
I might not be able to go home.

21
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,640
It's no big deal.

22
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,160
Since you guys have to tutor together these next few days anyway,

23
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,440
and it's a hassle to go back and forth every day,

24
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,560
why don't you just stay here?

25
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,560
Make yourself at home. Don't be shy.

26
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,760
No, it's fine, Auntie. I...

27
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,840
What do you mean 'no need'?

28
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,240
It's so late and you don't have your keys.

29
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,370
Where are you going?

30
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,440
Just listen to me.

31
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:17,800
But Mom,

32
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,400
our place is so small. Where will he sleep?

33
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,200
This child.

34
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,079
Why are you being so unreasonable?

35
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:25,680
Jingu came all the way here to tutor you.

36
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,640
And we haven't even paid him yet.

37
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:34,640
This sofa is made of wood, it's really impossible to sleep on.

38
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,840
I won't trouble you, Auntie.

39
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,800
I can stay in a hotel. I have money.

40
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,440
Why spend that money?

41
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,680
It's not like we don't have enough room.

42
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,640
Mom.

43
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:44,960
You...

44
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,400
Qingyun's bed is big.

45
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,370
How about you two

46
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,160
sleep here? It's big enough.

47
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:49,960
You are both grown-ups.

48
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,440
It shouldn't be inconvenient.

49
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,500
It's settled then.

50
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,720
No, no.

51
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:54,600
Mom.

52
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,100
Don't 'Mom' me.

53
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:58,560
If not, you can sleep on the sofa.

54
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,840
Jingu, in the bathroom...

55
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,410
We have all the toiletries.

56
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:07,320
I'll go find you a set of pajamas.

57
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,000
They're Qingyun's.

58
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,200
You two are about the same height,

59
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,160
they'll definitely fit.

60
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,000
They're brand new.

61
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,280
Ma'am, I...

62
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:18,800
Then,

63
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,079
sorry to trouble you.

64
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,060
You have to at least give me a blanket.

65
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:31,450
Let me make this clear upfront.

66
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:34,040
If you dare to fart, snore,

67
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,280
or cross this line,

68
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,760
I'll kick you off the bed.

69
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:40,120
That's what I wanted to tell you too.

70
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,160
Mom,

71
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,600
is the food ready?

72
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,860
I'm starving to death.

73
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,130
What... What are you doing?

74
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,810
What are you eating this early in the morning?

75
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:14,960
Good morning, Auntie.

76
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:15,680
Morning, Grandpa. Morning, Yuanbao.

77
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,840
Yuanbao, come on, sit.

78
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:17,520
Time to eat, Bao.

79
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,280
Let's eat.

80
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,160
You two...

81
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,320
Guo...

82
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:29,000
You... didn't you go home yesterday?

83
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,250
I couldn't find my keys.

84
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,930
My parents went to Beijing.

85
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:37,480
So you two shared a bed all night?

86
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,320
Come, sit.

87
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,360
They slept in Qingyun's bed yesterday.

88
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,760
Eat up. Don't dawdle.

89
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,040
Jingu is here too.

90
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,280
That's great.

91
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,760
Come, let's eat.

92
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,200
Morning, Grandma.

93
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,440
Morning.

94
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,800
Have some congee.

95
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:11,480
Sit.

96
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,200
Okay.

97
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,720
Here, one pair for each.

98
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,860
Thank you, Auntie.

99
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:22,000
Recently, they've been tutoring together.

100
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,400
Jingu's parents went to Beijing again.

101
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,720
Jingu, just stay here.

102
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,100
Make yourself at home.

103
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:32,130
It'll be easier for you to study together.

104
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,840
The Olympics are coming up.

105
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,720
We can watch them together.

106
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,040
It'll be fun.

107
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,000
Sorry for the trouble, Auntie.

108
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,480
Will I be bothering you?

109
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,320
I actually think so.

110
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,560
You dawdle like a girl.

111
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,440
Your classmate is tutoring you and can't go home.

112
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,040
Shouldn't he stay here?

113
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:52,000
You have no manners.

114
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:55,200
Auntie, I'd better stay in a hotel.

115
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,040
No.

116
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,920
Listen to me and stay here.

117
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,160
A hotel isn't as comfortable as home.

118
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,120
Exactly.

119
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:04,040
You can study and progress together.

120
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,920
It's like a happy family.

121
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:09,040
Grandma will cook for you every day.

122
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,680
Exactly.

123
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,040
Seeing you guys,

124
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,300
makes me feel like I'm seeing Xiaoyu.

125
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,240
You guys

126
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,320
are all his classmates.

127
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,920
This kind of friendship is so precious.

128
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,960
Here, Jingu, eat more.

129
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,120
Here, Jingu.

130
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,720
Have some dough sticks.

131
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,850
Thank you, Grandpa.

132
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,240
Alright then.

133
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:29,880
Here, have an egg.

134
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:30,680
Thank you, Auntie.

135
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,760
You're welcome.

136
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,240
Grandma, here,

137
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,400
try this.

138
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,600
Jingu, you're so sweet.

139
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,580
Grandma, eat this.

140
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,480
This is good.

141
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,900
Qingyun, you've grown sensible too.

142
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,840
Here, eat this, Grandma.

143
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,060
This is delicious.

144
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,080
Jingu,

145
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:58,320
how are you so good at studying?

146
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,520
This one is tastier. Have some.

147
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,850
Here, have some greens.

148
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,480
Grandma.

149
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,000
Grandma. Grandma.

150
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:07,720
Grandma.

151
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,160
Grandma.

152
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,320
Global cooling.

153
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,560
Which one of you two young men

154
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,840
can help Grandma change a lightbulb?

155
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,600
Grandma, I'll do it.

156
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,400
Jingu, you can do anything.

157
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:41,600
Let's go, Grandma.

158
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,920
When our Yuanbao grows up,

159
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:45,600
she needs to find someone who can do anything.

160
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,400
Grandma, I'll do it.

161
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,080
Why is this tile cracked?

162
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,640
Why is this table broken?

163
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,560
When did this glass break?

164
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,320
Why is this wall dirty?

165
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,800
Is this my house?

166
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,560
It's so clean.

167
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,340
You are so capable.

168
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,080
Let's form a contracting team.

169
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,200
Let's form a contracting team.

170
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,260
We'll definitely make a lot of money.

171
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:02,480
Ten.

172
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,440
Five.

173
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,240
I love you, China.

174
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,560
I love you, China.

175
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,440
Go China!

176
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:28,560
I love you, China.

177
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:35,520
I love you, China.

178
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:42,320
I will dedicate my most beautiful youth to you,

179
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:45,720
my mother,

180
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:51,040
my motherland.

181
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,000
So beautiful.

182
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,560
When we go to college in Beijing,

183
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:32,160
I'll take you to see the Bird's Nest, okay?

184
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,360
With your grades,

185
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,170
you still want to go to Beijing?

186
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:38,240
Just wait and see. I will definitely get in.

187
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,440
Okay, then it's a deal.

188
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:42,760
It's a deal.

189
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,920
Go China!

190
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,680
Go seniors!

191
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,400
Senior year, here we come.

192
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,920
Welcome back, class.

193
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,560
Starting today,

194
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:11,820
we officially enter our senior year.

195
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,040
Which means

196
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,280
we need to start preparing for the Gaokao.

197
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,760
Senior year is not like your first two years.

198
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,240
After we finish the new lessons...

199
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:20,160
We will have four rounds of general review,

200
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,840
so I hope you can all

201
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,000
keep up with me.

202
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:23,760
I don't want

203
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,160
any of you to fall behind.

204
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,290
For senior year,

205
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:28,320
besides an extra hour of evening study,

206
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,120
each weekend,

207
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,420
you'll only have Sunday afternoons off.

208
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,170
So that means

209
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,840
we have no rest time at all.

210
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:34,520
Yeah.

211
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:37,440
Then P.E. classes are completely out of the question.

212
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,100
All right, stop complaining.

213
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,520
During your senior year,

214
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,480
aside from eating, sleeping, and using the bathroom,

215
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:44,880
you must all swim in the ocean of knowledge.

216
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,280
As for those who are good swimmers,

217
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,160
don't be arrogant.

218
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:49,120
Because haven't you heard?

219
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,000
Good swimmers are the ones who drown.

220
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
Carelessness will cost you dearly.

221
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,300
As for those who can only doggy paddle...

222
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,400
Don't lose heart.

223
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,920
Maybe as you keep paddling,

224
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,560
you'll become a champion swimmer.

225
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:01,160
Anyway, in this senior year,

226
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,080
you must swim to the shores of your dreams.

227
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:04,880
Keep it up!

228
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,000
Keep it up!

229
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,730
Also, an announcement.

230
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:10,000
The annual National Physics Competition

231
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,160
is about to begin.

232
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,840
You all know this competition is

233
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:13,720
very fierce.

234
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:16,240
Not only middle and high school students,

235
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,400
but also college students.

236
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,640
However, this is currently the

237
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,600
most prestigious national physics competition.

238
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,880
Moreover, the competition results

239
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,560
are internationally recognized.

240
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,360
I heard the prize money this time

241
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,400
is around 100,000 yuan.

242
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,840
100,000.

243
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:32,880
Each school only has one spot.

244
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,080
Based on our class's past performance,

245
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,400
I recommend Meng Jingu.

246
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,960
Does anyone have any objections?

247
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,440
No, no, no.

248
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,440
Meng Jingu, you have no problem with it, right?

249
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,440
When I announced it just now,

250
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,680
you looked worried.

251
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:50,560
Do you have any concerns?

252
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:54,240
I think someone else is more suitable than me.

253
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:54,960
Who?

254
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,200
Mu Qingjun.

255
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,720
Mu... Mu Qingjun.

256
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:02,120
These are the physics problems we made for each other

257
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:04,400
when we were pen pals before we met.

258
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,240
Take a look.

259
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,720
When I first transferred here,

260
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,180
in our first monthly exam,

261
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,680
there was a difficult physics question.

262
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,609
Do you remember?

263
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:11,650
Yes, I remember.

264
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,440
I remember I was sitting behind him.

265
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,359
I saw he finished that question first.

266
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,760
So he didn't copy mine.

267
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,880
But he admitted he cheated,

268
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,440
so I didn't say anything.

269
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,880
That's impossible.

270
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,720
Why would he admit he cheated

271
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,080
and always finish at the bottom?

272
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:32,800
Actually, he is a genius.

273
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:35,520
So I don't want his talent to be buried.

274
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,080
If you don't believe me, sir,

275
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,880
you can compare it with his previous handwriting.

276
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,900
As to why, I'm not really sure either.

277
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,240
But I promised him

278
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,650
I would keep his secret.

279
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,640
Okay, I understand.

280
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,480
I won't mention this to him.

281
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:04,160
You go back first. I'll think of something.

282
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,040
Yuanbao.

283
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:18,080
Auntie, why are you here?

284
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,640
I cut some fruit for you.

285
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:20,520
Here, try it.

286
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:25,100
Is it sweet?

287
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,490
Yes. Thank you, Auntie.

288
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,840
Where are Grandpa and Grandma? Did they go out?

289
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,300
They went square dancing.

290
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,180
Ever since Grandpa Gong moved in,

291
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,480
Grandma's mental state has been much better.

292
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:39,740
The two of them can look after each other.

293
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,040
When you go to college in the future,

294
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,840
we won't be so worried.

295
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,280
They were talking and laughing,

296
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,680
and I was quite happy too.

297
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,320
Yuanbao.

298
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:55,360
Your uncle is pulling strings in the UK now,

299
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:58,970
trying to apply for study abroad quotas for you and Qingyun.

300
00:18:59,040 --> 00:18:59,840
I heard

301
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,760
it's a very good university.

302
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:03,800
With the current study abroad fever,

303
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,280
many people who come back from abroad

304
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:07,160
can find very good jobs.

305
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:10,680
Your uncle and I have to plan for you.

306
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:12,280
Don't you think?

307
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:16,600
Auntie, if we study abroad,

308
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:19,450
will Grandpa and Grandma go together?

309
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,780
Grandpa and Grandma are getting old.

310
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,820
If they suddenly go to a new environment,

311
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,840
they might not adapt to it.

312
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:34,360
So we can't take Grandpa and Grandma with us.

313
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,000
Your uncle and I

314
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,810
are also struggling with this.

315
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,930
After all, we are not familiar with the place.

316
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,290
Your uncle's job has just stabilized.

317
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,520
Taking care of such a big family

318
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,520
is indeed very stressful.

319
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:50,600
Auntie.

320
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,640
I only have Grandma.

321
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,120
If I go abroad,

322
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,610
and something happens to Grandma,

323
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,900
I wouldn't be able to come back in a hurry.

324
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,560
Don't worry.

325
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,580
This hasn't been decided yet.

326
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:08,640
Auntie is just

327
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,720
analyzing it objectively with you.

328
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,520
If we really go abroad,

329
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,800
we are not going there to enjoy life.

330
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,770
You and Qingyun will have classes,

331
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,880
and your uncle and I will have to work.

332
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:21,000
Leaving Grandpa and Grandma at home alone,

333
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,530
surrounded by foreigners,

334
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:24,400
and they don't speak the language.

335
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:27,120
If they want to go out to buy groceries or take a walk,

336
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,380
it would be difficult.

337
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:30,720
Arriving in a new environment,

338
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,120
leaving their hometown,

339
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:35,080
is really not a good thing for the elderly.

340
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:39,960
Auntie.

341
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,200
Then I won't go.

342
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,360
Okay.

343
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:51,720
This hasn't been finalized yet.

344
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:54,130
Your uncle just went to pull some strings.

345
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:56,040
It might not even work out.

346
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,840
Don't be nervous.

347
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,280
Auntie promises you

348
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,880
that I will arrange everything properly.

349
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:04,840
Okay?

350
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,980
It's late. Go to bed early.

351
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,600
Eat those fruits before you go to sleep.

352
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:11,920
Don't waste them.

353
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,500
Auntie is leaving.

354
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,120
Classmates.

355
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,000
Through the school leaders,

356
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,920
After a meeting with all the physics teachers,

357
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,120
the spot to represent our school

358
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,040
in the National Physics Competition

359
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,160
has fallen to our class.

360
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,240
This person is...

361
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,400
Mu Qingjun.

362
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,760
Mu Qingjun?

363
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:38,040
That's right, Mu Qingjun.

364
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:40,760
Mr. Tian,

365
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,400
I think you must be mistaken.

366
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:45,800
Mu Qingjun and I grew up together.

367
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,360
I know his level better than anyone.

368
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,800
His physics homework,

369
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:53,720
I even helped him with it at home.

370
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:57,200
If you ask him to participate in the National Physics Competition,

371
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,860
wouldn't that embarrass him?

372
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,160
Exactly, sir.

373
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,920
With Yuanbao's grades,

374
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,800
his tutoring would make him dead last every time.

375
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,080
I don't believe it either.

376
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,120
Let alone you,

377
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:08,120
at first, I didn't believe it either.

378
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,520
But now it's been proven.

379
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,440
This kid is really impressive.

380
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:12,520
Not only is he good at physics,

381
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,980
he's even better at acting. He fooled us all.

382
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,160
Yuanbao, he grew up with you.

383
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:19,120
And you didn't even know his true level.

384
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,160
You tell me, how good is his act?

385
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,880
How is this possible?

386
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:25,800
Why would he pretend?

387
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,600
There's no reason, sir.

388
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,410
I don't know about that.

389
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:31,080
But that doesn't matter now.

390
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,160
The important thing is

391
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,400
that he has been listed by the school

392
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,880
as a key student for cultivation.

393
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:35,800
You should also work hard.

394
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:36,460
Have a seat.

395
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,680
Really?

396
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,920
He was just pretending to be bad at studying?

397
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:42,580
Even Yuanbao, who grew up with him, didn't know.

398
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,400
All right.

399
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,360
It's a good thing that Mu Qingjun is good at studying.

400
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:46,720
When you are with him,

401
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,290
you can also learn from him.

402
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:51,610
Mu Qingjun, you came at the right time.

403
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:53,000
I happen to have a few copies

404
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,280
of previous National Physics Competition papers.

405
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,040
Take a look.

406
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:56,800
No.

407
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,800
Why are you showing me this?

408
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,130
I don't know how to do it.

409
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:02,220
Still pretending?

410
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:06,620
Come, look at this.

411
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,180
Look for yourself.

412
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:16,720
No, this...

413
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:20,440
This isn't mine. Sir,

414
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,800
you made a mistake.

415
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:23,720
Mistake? Impossible.

416
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,280
With this spider-like handwriting of yours,

417
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,410
I compared so many before I caught you.

418
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,920
Sir, you know what my level is.

419
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,120
You know that.

420
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:34,120
How could this be mine?

421
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:36,000
I didn't know your level before,

422
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,700
but I understand it today.

423
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:40,920
Sir, what do I have to say for you to believe me?

424
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,760
I don't know anything anyway.

425
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,160
Don't expect me to win glory for the school.

426
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,840
I don't have that ability.

427
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:47,560
Mu Qingjun.

428
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:49,880
Don't be in a hurry to refuse.

429
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,400
Now this matter,

430
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,040
has already spread in the school.

431
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:54,800
They say you are a hidden genius.

432
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,640
Whether you go to this competition or not,

433
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,760
this matter is a done deal.

434
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:00,400
If you don't go,

435
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:03,240
many students will definitely think you are very selfish,

436
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,440
unwilling to contribute to the school.

437
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,520
Stop sighing.

438
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:07,520
You study so well,

439
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:08,920
and you deceived all the teachers.

440
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:09,720
Why?

441
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:12,360
No, how did you get this?

442
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,600
Did Meng Jingu give it to you?

443
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:17,560
It was me.

444
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,720
What do you mean? Are you crazy?

445
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,040
Don't be angry first.

446
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:28,560
This time, due to personal reasons,

447
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,680
I can't participate in this competition.

448
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,800
Setting aside winning glory for the school,

449
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:34,680
this competition is indeed very important

450
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,120
for your future college applications.

451
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,440
Rather than letting a mediocre person waste the opportunity,

452
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,640
it's better if you go.

453
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,640
There's only one chance in high school.

454
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,900
You should cherish it.

455
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,040
Just work hard for your future self.

456
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:49,100
Do you need to worry about my affairs?

457
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,240
Why didn't you ask me first?

458
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,120
If I asked you, would you go?

459
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:51,920
Of course not.

460
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:52,880
Then that's it.

461
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:56,480
You,

462
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:57,360
Mu Qingjun.

463
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,560
you really messed me up.

464
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,560
I really don't understand.

465
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,880
Isn't it good to be a good student cared for by teachers?

466
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:04,600
Mu Qingjun.

467
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:05,440
Mu Qingjun!

468
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:07,440
Mu Qingyun is a physics genius.

469
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,640
He kept it from everyone before.

470
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:11,360
Even the teachers just found out.

471
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:14,200
They even asked him to join the National Physics Olympiad.

472
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,000
No way.

473
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:17,280
Others might not know,

474
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:18,640
but how could Xiong Yuanbao not know?

475
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,920
They are so close.

476
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,040
Mu Qingyun wouldn't hide it from her, right?

477
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:23,240
Not necessarily.

478
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:24,600
Judging by her expression,

479
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,200
she doesn't look like she knows.

480
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,240
That shouldn't be.

481
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:29,680
Mu Qingyun and Xiong Yuanbao

482
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,800
are childhood sweethearts.

483
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:31,860
For such a big deal,

484
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,400
Mu Qingyun wouldn't keep it from her.

485
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,000
I think it's just Xiong Yuanbao

486
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,520
who keeps pestering Mu Qingyun.

487
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:38,080
When Mu Qingyun was bad at studying,

488
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:40,280
they didn't look out of place together.

489
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,760
But things are different now.

490
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:44,020
Mu Qingyun is now the top guy at Zhicheng.

491
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,560
He's good-looking and great at studying.

492
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,960
He's literally the male lead out of a novel.

493
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,440
They look so awkward

494
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,160
standing together.

495
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:03,760
Yuanbao.

496
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,400
Mom promises you,

497
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:08,040
I will be back soon.

498
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:15,210
You remember the Diamond Princess

499
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:17,010
and the Elf's Appointment.

500
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,810
Why don't you remember that I hate being lied to the most?

501
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:24,560
Yuanbao.

502
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,090
Get out of my way.

503
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:28,440
Yuanbao, listen to me.

504
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,760
I really didn't mean to hide it from you.

505
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:32,200
Do you know that

506
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:35,330
I hate it the most when people lie to me?

507
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:37,600
I know.

508
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,320
Then do you remember

509
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,160
that you swore

510
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,000
never to lie to me?

511
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,360
I remember.

512
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:46,770
All these years,

513
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,130
you dragged me to tutor you,

514
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:52,480
pretending to know nothing.

515
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,320
Watching me rack my brains to teach you

516
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,200
and explain problems to you...

517
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,840
Did you find it amusing?

518
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,000
No.

519
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:01,880
It's not like that, Yuanbao.

520
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,050
I rejected Mr. Tian.

521
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:04,520
They got it wrong.

522
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:07,240
If Mr. Tian hadn't mentioned it in class today,

523
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:10,010
how long were you going to lie to me?

524
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:14,280
What? Were you planning to amaze everyone

525
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:15,880
during the college entrance exam

526
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:18,080
and crush me with your genius scores?

527
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,730
No, Yuanbao.

528
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,530
I really never thought of that.

529
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,690
Watching a poor student like me

530
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:26,540
rack my brains to teach a genius like you,

531
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,440
playing me for a fool...

532
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:30,040
Is it fun?

533
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,620
When I argued with Mr. Tian

534
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:38,370
because I was afraid you'd make a fool of yourself...

535
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:41,360
It seems I am the biggest joke.

536
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,800
A poor student like me is too stupid

537
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:48,210
to understand these twists and turns.

538
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,660
How do I deserve to be friends with a genius like you?

539
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,040
Yuanbao.

540
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:57,920
Are you okay?

541
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:16,450
Grandma.

542
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:17,760
Why didn't you wake me up?

543
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,290
I'm almost late for school.

544
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,840
I called you several times.

545
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:21,800
You slept like a pig

546
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:23,520
and just refused to get up.

547
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:28,320
Here, take these two apples.

548
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,720
I don't need the apples.

549
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:32,880
You haven't eaten any fruit for days.

550
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:35,360
Take them to school and share them with Qingjun.

551
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:36,520
Okay, I got it.

552
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:37,720
Be careful on the way.

553
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:39,080
I got it.

554
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,280
Come home early after school.

555
00:28:40,280 --> 00:28:41,160
I'll wait for you for dinner.

556
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,000
Okay.

557
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,280
I got it, Grandma.

558
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,050
I'm leaving.

559
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:12,240
Since that happened,

560
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:14,930
we haven't spoken a word to each other.

561
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,680
We've never been like this

562
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,800
before.

563
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,290
The person I trusted so much

564
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:23,090
lied to me for so many years.

565
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:26,400
Every time I mocked his grades in the past,

566
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:29,320
every time I tried hard to tutor him,

567
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:32,090
and every time I worried about his future,

568
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:33,800
looking back now,

569
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,920
it all feels like a huge irony.

570
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,840
And for the first time,

571
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,960
I feel so distant from him.

572
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,400
Across this short distance,

573
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:46,120
it's like a galaxy between us.

574
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,530
Yuanbao, what's wrong?

575
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:58,520
I'm fine.

576
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,500
Are you okay, Yuanbao?

577
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:02,200
I'm fine, sir.

578
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:04,320
Do you want to go to the infirmary?

579
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:05,080
No need.

580
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:09,320
Sorry, Mr. Xu.

581
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,800
I need to talk to Yuanbao about something.

582
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:11,800
Then you can go.

583
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:23,440
Sir, what do you need me for?

584
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:24,560
Yuanbao,

585
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,180
your grandmother is sick.

586
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:29,360
She just came out of the emergency room

587
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,560
and was sent to the intensive care unit.

588
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:33,800
Grandma.

589
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:35,200
Yuanbao.

590
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,040
Grandma was fine this morning.

591
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,330
How did this happen?

592
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,140
Why is this happening?

593
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,960
The doctor said it's a heart problem.

594
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,680
But we don't know the exact disease yet.

595
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:59,360
We have to wait for the results to be sure.

596
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:05,680
Auntie,

597
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:09,720
is my grandma in danger?

598
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:12,760
I don't know.

599
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:19,840
Doctor,

600
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,920
how are the test results?

601
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:26,320
The aorta close to the human heart

602
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:29,090
is called the thoracic aorta or ascending aorta.

603
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:32,000
It consists of the intima, media, and adventitia.

604
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,680
For various reasons,

605
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:35,720
the vascular intima tears.

606
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,840
Blood flows through the tear

607
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:40,400
into the inner layer of the aorta,

608
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:41,780
forming a false lumen.

609
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:44,400
If blood continuously flows into this false lumen

610
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,520
and cannot get out,

611
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:48,400
it will keep tearing the blood vessel wall

612
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:50,400
until the adventitia ruptures.

613
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:51,960
Doctor,

614
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,320
is it a very serious disease?

615
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,000
It is quite a dangerous condition.

616
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:01,330
Once the aortic dissection ruptures,

617
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:04,640
the patient is prone to hemorrhagic shock,

618
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,520
or even sudden death.

619
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,800
If it ruptures into the thoracic cavity,

620
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:12,280
hemothorax or hemoptysis will occur.

621
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,040
In short, it's very serious.

622
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:14,960
Doctor,

623
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,560
if we do surgery,

624
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:18,600
will she recover?

625
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,240
Don't worry.

626
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:21,320
We will

627
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:23,640
develop the best treatment plan.

628
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,970
But because the patient is too old,

629
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,370
the top priority now

630
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,960
is to control her blood pressure.

631
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,200
We need to stabilize her condition.

632
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:32,460
We absolutely cannot rush into surgery.

633
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:35,770
I'm afraid she won't make it off the operating table.

634
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:38,760
What are my grandmother's chances of survival?
